<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en-US">
<head>
  <title>Brave UX - Work - Independent Journal Review</title>
  <%- include ../partials/_head %>
</head>
<body>
  <%- include ../partials/_menu %>
  <main class="wrapper case-study ijr">
    <header class="case-header overlay">
      <div class="case-header-content container">
        <h5 class="case-header-client-name">Independent Journal Review</h5>
        <h1 class="case-header-tagline">Redesigning your&nbsp;<br />morning paper</h1>
        <h6 class="case-header-type">Social-First, Mobile-First News Platform</h6>
      </div>
    </header>

    <section class="case-exec-summary padded dark-blue">
      <div class="container">
        <p class="case-exec-summary-text">We designed an interface for <em>Independent Journal Review</em>, a news publishing platform that averages over 40 million visitors each month.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-breakdown padded blue">
      <div class="container row between">
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Challenge</p>
          <h3 class="case-breakdown-summary">
            What is <em>Independent Journal Review</em>?
          </h3>
          <p class="case-breakdown-detail">
            Social media drives more traffic to the <em>Independent Journal Review</em> platform than any other source. Our job was to decrease the drop-off rate and increase brand recognition.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Solution</p>
          <h3 class="case-breakdown-summary">
            A cut above the rest
          </h3>
          <p class="case-breakdown-detail">
            The clean, cohesive, and fully responsive experience provides much needed clarity for the user and credibility for the publication.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="case-breakdown-box column gutter">
          <p class="case-breakdown-heading">Scope</p>
          <ul class="case-breakdown-list">
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">Brand System</li>
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">Information Architecture</li>
            <li class="case-breakdown-list-item">Interaction Design</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block padded-top gray">
      <div class="row container">
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md column half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="inner-block-content gutter-right padded-bottom">
            <h2 class="case-block-heading">A lighter take on timely news</h2>
            <p class="case-block-text">
              The previous platform was dark and difficult to navigate. We provided a new unified interface system that made reading bright, welcoming, and easy.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block column half-md two-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="frame frame-desktop shadow dark edge-bottom sr-bottom">
            <img src="./images/work/ijr/homepage-old.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block padded yellow">
      <div class="row container">
        <div class="inner-block column half-md two-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="frame frame-tablet dark sr-left">
            <div class="frame-container">
              <img src="./images/work/ijr/tablet.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md gutter-bottom-mobile column order-top-xs half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="inner-block-content gutter-left">
            <h2 class="case-block-heading">More than just a pretty face</h2>
            <p class="case-block-text">
              We architected a layout to present stories by topic as a more engaging and intuitive way to group articles than the standard feed.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block row padded gray">
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md gutter-bottom-mobile column half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="inner-block-content">
              <h2 class="case-block-heading">The story is the experience</h2>
              <p class="case-block-text">
                We made the story king, keeping related items and share links on the side. Why? We want users to have the best content experience possible.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block column half-md two-third-lg half-xl gutter-left-mobile">
          <div class="frame frame-desktop shadow dark edge-right sr-right">
            <img src="./images/work/ijr/homepage-new.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
          </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block row padded-top dark-blue">
      <div class="inner-block gutter-right-mobile column half-md two-third-lg half-xl ijr-display">
        <img src="./images/work/ijr/multi-display-container.svg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
        <div class="frame frame-desktop dark edge-left absolute sr-left">
          <img src="./images/work/ijr/multi-display-onbot.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
        </div>
        <div class="frame frame-desktop dark absolute sr-bottom sr-delay">
          <img src="./images/work/ijr/multi-display-ontop.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md column order-top-xs half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="inner-block-content padded-bottom">
            <h2 class="case-block-heading">Putting more than a face to a name</h2>
            <p class="case-block-text">
              An About section should answer not just “who?” but also “why?” It’s a testimony to the heart and culture of an organization. We included fun facts, stats, and plenty of photos to more effectively tell their story.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="block row padded gray">
        <div class="inner-block absolute-center-md gutter-bottom-mobile column half-md one-third-lg half-xl">
          <div class="container">
            <div class="inner-block-content">
              <h2 class="case-block-heading">Mobile, desktop, and everything in between</h2>
              <p class="case-block-text">
                We’ve got responsive on lock. Starting mobile-first, we architected a user experience that’s beautiful and functional from pocket to widescreen.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="inner-block column half-md two-third-lg half-xl gutter-left-mobile ijr-article">
          <div class="frame frame-desktop shadow dark edge-right sr-right">
            <img src="./images/work/ijr/article-desktop.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
          </div>
          <div class="frame frame-mobile shadow absolute dark sr-bottom sr-delay">
            <div class="frame-container">
              <img src="./images/work/ijr/article-mobile.jpg" alt="" class="inner-block-image contain">
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="case-referral row">
      <div class="inner-block padded column absolute-center-xs half-md dark-blue">
        <div class="container">
          <p class="case-referral-blockquote">When you hire Brave, you get the Navy Seals of User Experience...</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inner-block padded column half-md blue">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="case-referral-quote-icon"></div>
          <p class="case-referral-text">When you hire Brave, you get the Navy Seals of User Experience: a highly skilled group of experts who precisely navigate the mission you give them. They immediately get to work after deeply understanding your organization’s goals, and quickly deliver what you thought was close to impossible: satisfying all the internal stakeholders while, more importantly, designing an experience that sends the user on a journey that keeps them happy, returning, and ultimately having more brand affinity.</p>
          <p class="case-referral-author">Carl Sceusa, <em>Chief Technology Officer, Independent Journal Review</em></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="cta-block padded">
      <a href="./work/idauto" class="cta-button cta-button-left" title="Previous Case">Previous Case</a>
      <div class="cta-content container">
        <div class="container">
          <div class="cta-text">Sometimes, you find something that just works.</div>
          <a href="/approach/" class="btn btn-text icon-arrow">See Our Approach</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <a href="./work/foh" class="cta-button cta-button-right" title="Next Case">Next Case</a>
    </section>

    <%- include ../partials/_footer %>
  </main>

  <%- include ../partials/_footer-scripts %>

</body>
</html>
